          "type": "incorrect_translation",
          "description": "The Azerbaijani translation uses a passive verb form 'Nəzərdən keçirilir' (being reviewed/under review) rather than an active form. In the context of access rights labels, 'reviewing' should indicate the user's capability to perform the action, not a passive state. The translation should use an active form like 'Nəzərdən keçmə' (reviewing) or 'İncelə' (review) to match the active meaning of the English label.",
